       The next seven chapters provide information for application   |
       developers about the OSF/Motif Window Manager.  The           |
       OSF/Motif Window Manager (MWM) provides window management     |
       facilities within the framework of the OSF/Motif environ-
       ment.  MWM provides you with an industry standard user
       interface, a high degree of flexibility, and a pleasing
       visual interface.

       MWM facilitates user-computer communications in the follow-
       ing areas:

          +o MWM provides for direct manipulation of graphic objects
            using an object-action model.  A user controls the
            operation of an application program by selecting a win-
            dow, menu, icon, or other graphic object and then indi-
            cating an action to be done to that object.              |

          +o MWM uses several configuration files, including ....XXXXddddeeee----    |
            ffffaaaauuuullllttttssss, ....mmmmwwwwmmmmrrrrcccc, and ....mmmmoooottttiiiiffffbbbbiiiinnnndddd.  By editing these        |
            files, users can customize the appearance and behavior   |
            of MWM.

          +o MWM provides keyboard access to window management func-  |
            tionality in cases where a mouse is not available or     |
            the user prefers keyboard access.

